{
  "stem": "1975.4",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 54.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I was very proud to be now in the army, whereby I'm going to be participating in a certain way, in a-- in a very minimal way to be able to take some vengeance from those who, who have punished me, and who have done so much harm to myself and to my dear ones.",
      "word_count": 56
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It was really like a blessing.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Especially-- you're young, and you are looking forward, you know.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I, I took it very, very easy, you know, the, the, the, the training and the, the kilometers that we had to walk with all the ammunition, and the, the target shooting, and the, the topography.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They gave us all instruction because we're supposed to be future, future officers in the army.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They, they felt that, with the kind of education that we had and the kind of experience-- life experience-- we-- they-- and, and the fast absorbing of all this preparation, they felt that-- the only thing, the only point which I was concerned is whereby in the-- in the next month to come, they wanted very badly I should join the, the Communist Party.",
      "word_count": 64
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Which-- most of the members of this elite group were members of the party.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And I mentioned to my officer who was-- after, after that-- that was a captain.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But then I had a officer whom I-- I'm suspicious that he was Jewish.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "His name was Vinokurov.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And for some reason, I mean, he was very, very, very, extremely friendly to me.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And I-- and I had a, a, a feeling that he was-- he was Jewish, although nobody knew, actually, his whereabouts, yeah.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "He was a colonel.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And he always used to treat me very, very specially.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Now, the first mission what we had is in the vicinity of Kaunas.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
